articles.title: G20 summit boycotted by US closes in South Africa - BBC
articles.description: South African President Cyril Ramaphosa says there is a "renewed commitment to multilateral co-operation".
articles.content:
The G20 summit in South Africa, a gathering of the world's major economies, has ended with a joint declaration committing to "multilateral co-operation".
